{
  "stem": "5810.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I think they were-- were willing to help wherever they could.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I don't know to this day if-- if that's absolutely true, except for one teacher, because he saved my life many times.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But I believe that the administration accepted these falsified papers with the full knowledge of who I was.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because I also do remember, there were many searches by the SS and the Gestapo in the schools.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "When they knew that Jewish children were enrolled in Catholic schools and hiding under guise with different names and so on.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And of course the searchers were-- and the only way they could have known, is to drop your pants and only Jewish boys was circumcised in those days.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that's how they-- many, many children, I know one at least, a good friend of mine, was taken away because that happened.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But the administration seemed to know when those things were going to happen, or at least the principal did.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I remember many times the principal walking into class and calling me out for whatever reason, and to wind up in the infirmary, or hidden in his office, or whatever, so that whenever there was a search they wouldn't see that I was a Jewish boy.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, again, it-- it would have been the end of 1942 into 1943 at that point.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I would say more 1943, because there were a few months of 1942 that I never got out, so yes, 1943.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right through liberation.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The events in that Catholic school, I can't begin to tell you.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Well, actually what did happen to me, finally, because my Jewish upbringing at that age couldn't have been very strong.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My character was being formed and I was no longer being raised.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My father was dead.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
